ix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kupwerstix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scribe</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(5/18/02 2:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=66.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Revenge</span><hr size=1> Another fine day in the guildhall it seemed it was going to be.<br>
Kupwerstix sat in the corner and softly strumming his lute, watching his friends argue over who had the best looking armor. Kupwerstix snickered softly at the absurdity of the argument. Then a young elf ran into the room bearing a letter. &quot;Lord Sharpnote, i have a letter for you from Kelethin!&quot; the boy said quickly. Kupwerstix stood up and took the note from the boy, and flipped a gold piece to him. He opened the letter and read it slowly. He angrily crumbled the letter in his hand. Tears running down his cheek, he grabbed his drum and ran out of the guildhall. The world sped by him as he ran on. He ran until he at last found his favorite tree and he sat at the base of it and began to sing a song, a song of mourning. The letter was a notice from kelethin that his family had been  murdered by some Teir'dal. They had not seen his face, so they knew not who it was who committed the crime. Kupwerstix knew what him must do, he would travel to Kelethin to see his mother , father , and brother be put to rest. Then he would travel to Neriak to find this murderer, it would take time, he knew that, but revenge was a dish best served cold. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#AB8C5B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ublahg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Blahg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scribe Master</span><br>  Posts: 107<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(5/18/02 5:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=66.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Revenge</span><hr size=1> Blahg watched from a corner as Kupwerstix ran from the guildhall, wondering what had happened.  Later that day, another sad messenger came looking for the bard, and not finding him, left a similar message for him with the guild.<br>
<br>
Standing and wiping grime from a large and rusty sledge, which he had begun to favor over his old swords, Blahg stormed from the guildhall in search of this lost bard.  The Teir'dal shall pay for this crime, their evil ways must be put to an end. <p><html>
