<br>
&quot;Hmmmm,&quot; Muttered Aryllyian, &quot;Adamantite.....this points to Neriak.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
_________<br>
<br>
&quot;Let the ravens dine upon your innards!!&quot; Aryllyian spat hatred at the corpse of the Dark Elf guard upon the bridge.<br>
<br>
Minutes later Aryllyian approached the dark entrance to Neriak.  His days of hiding from the guards were over.  After bounding over a low fallen tree, he heads directly for the nearest guard.<br>
<br>
&quot;Tell Mistress Rea Morda, I seek an audience!&quot; Aryllyian punctuated his demand with a wicked sword blow, which sent the guard fleeing for his life.<br>
__________<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/belvenelite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aryllyian>Aryllyian</A> at: 5/30/02 10:59:57 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#AB8C5B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ukupwerstix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kupwerstix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scribe</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(5/26/02 9:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=66.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Revenge</span><hr size=1> Neriak- A strange Dark Elf walked into the commons. His gold armor was indeed odd for a normal Dark Elf , but this was not a normal Dark Elf. Kupwerstix , using his mask of deception, walked among the teir'dal with ease. He so  was blinded by anger and grief that he did not think about how out of place he seemed here. As he entered the Third Gate a group of guards approached him. &quot; What is your name and house commoner?&quot; one of the guards asked him. &quot; My name is Khelben of House Zzporza&quot;. Kupwerstix replied. &quot;Never heard of you.... in fact I have never heard of House Zzporza now that i think about it&quot; one guard said.&quot; I don't think you are a Dark Elf at all&quot;. Kupwerstix, knowing his cover was blown, decided to take the chance to strike now. Pulling out his blade and Mace, he started a song of victory,giving him strength and speed. He cut through the guards with ease, but he knew he did not have much time now. He pulled out his drum and started to sing a song of speed but he found he could not move, for his feet were bound in roots. He turned to see a group or Wizards laughing at him , as they all began to cast their spells. Knowing his time was up he took one last desperate chance and let his back and let loose a desperate dirge at them knocking all of them off their feet. Kupwerstix grinned, but only for a moment.All he felt was a sharp pain, when the mace struck him in the back of the head. He fell hard to the cold floor unconscious. He later awoke in a small cell guarded by 4 guards. This has not been a good day.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#BA9F70><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ublahg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Blahg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scribe Master</span><br>  Posts: 108<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(5/27/02 1:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=66.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Revenge</span><hr size=1> Blahg wandered through the forest, lost and alone.  Looking back, it would have been wise to hire a halfling guide to help him sneak near the city of Neriak.  Having been in too big of a hurry to catch up with Kupwerstix, he hurried on alone and took a wrong turn.<br>
<br>
Blahg sat down near a tree, wishing that Elrax or Lenian was with.  Surely one of them would know how to get to the city!  <br>
<br>
